SOME big banks have come out for sponsoring industrial exhibition and business forum in Coast Region, which has highest number of industries in the country. The TIB Development Bank, the CRDB Bank and the NMB agreed on MondayÂ to facilitate such major events scheduled to take place between 1st and 7th of October, in efforts to stimulate more investments for the country's industrial growth in the region. The CRDB Bank affirmed that it will be a main sponsor of the events. Currently, according to Coast Regional Commissioner, Evarist Ndikilo, the region has a total of 1,192 established industries, both large and small scale industries. It is expected that at a minimum a total of 400 firms operating in Coast, Morogoro, Dar es Salaam and Tanga region will take will participate at both business forum and exhibitions.